## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/intervalmapoverlaps">IntervalMapOverlaps</a> - Iterate over the overlaps of mapped intervals in two IntervalMaps.

The maps may be different, but the KeyT and Traits types should be the same.

Typical uses:


<ul>
<li>Test for overlap: bool overlap = IntervalMapOverlaps(a, b).<a href="#ad85fedf8fb1b786bf6ed0d3518790bae">valid()</a>;</li>
<li>Enumerate overlaps: for (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/intervalmapoverlaps">IntervalMapOverlaps</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/md5-cpp/#ac0eafdc9ee161b71e7af98af736952fd">I(a, b)</a>; I.valid() ; ++I) &#123; ... &#125;</li>
</ul>
